description:
**Problem**
\`crates/beads-rs/src/git/sync.rs\` imports \`crate::daemon::metrics\`, creating a reverse dependency from the git layer up into the daemon layer. This is a layering violation that blocks extracting git into its own crate (\`beads-git\`). Git sync/checkpoint should be pure infrastructure that the daemon calls INTO, not the other way around.

**Design**
Introduce a trait seam so git sync can report metrics without knowing about the daemon.

New file in what will become beads-git (for now, in \`beads-rs/src/git/\`):

\`\`\`rust
// git/observe.rs
pub trait SyncObserver: Send + Sync + 'static {
    fn on_fetch_start(&self) {}
    fn on_fetch_end(&self, elapsed_ms: u64) {}
    fn on_push_start(&self) {}
    fn on_push_end(&self, elapsed_ms: u64) {}
    fn on_merge_start(&self) {}
    fn on_merge_end(&self, beads_merged: usize) {}
}

pub struct NoopSyncObserver;
impl SyncObserver for NoopSyncObserver {}
\`\`\`

Thread the observer into \`SyncProcess\`:
\`\`\`rust
pub struct SyncProcess<Phase> {
    observer: Arc<dyn SyncObserver>,
    // ... existing fields
}
\`\`\`

Then in the daemon, implement the real observer that calls the existing metrics functions. Wire it in when constructing the SyncProcess from \`git_worker.rs\`.

**Acceptance**
- [ ] \`git/sync.rs\` has zero imports from \`crate::daemon\`
- [ ] New \`SyncObserver\` trait in \`git/observe.rs\` (or similar)
- [ ] \`SyncProcess\` accepts an \`Arc<dyn SyncObserver>\` parameter
- [ ] Daemon provides a concrete observer implementation wired to existing metrics
- [ ] \`NoopSyncObserver\` available for non-daemon contexts (tests, future library consumers)
- [ ] \`rg "crate::daemon" crates/beads-rs/src/git/\` returns zero matches
- [ ] \`cargo test\` passes
- [ ] Git sync behavior unchanged

**Files:** \`crates/beads-rs/src/git/sync.rs\`, \`crates/beads-rs/src/git/observe.rs\` (new), \`crates/beads-rs/src/daemon/git_worker.rs\`, \`crates/beads-rs/src/daemon/metrics.rs\`
